# Structured Logging & Immutable Audit Trails

## Rule
Critical milestones in the lifecycle of any P2P financial event must emit an explicit, highly structured audit log.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Use the native NestJS `Logger` (or an integrated structured logging engine, e.g. Pino/Winston wired through Nest) to trace, at minimum:
  - Operation **initiation** (e.g. transfer requested, escrow created)
  - **Processing/intermediate state** transitions (e.g. funds locked, signature verified)
  - **Final settlement** (success or terminal failure)
- Log entries must include searchable, structured, correlatable fields — at minimum `transactionId` and `userId` (or `walletId`/`escrowId` where relevant) — emitted as structured fields/context, not just interpolated into a free-text string.
- **Crucial restriction:** private keys, secrets, credentials, full JWTs, or unmasked sensitive user data (e.g. full account numbers, raw signatures) must never be printed to stdout/logs under any circumstance. Mask or omit these fields entirely.

## What to flag in review
- Financial state transitions (escrow lock, settlement, refund, dispute) with no corresponding `Logger.log`/`Logger.error` call marking that milestone.
- Logging calls that use only a free-text string with no structured context object (e.g. `this.logger.log('transfer done')` instead of `this.logger.log('transfer.settled', { transactionId, userId })`).
- Any `console.log`/`logger.debug` call that includes a private key, secret, full JWT, raw signature, or other sensitive field — even temporarily, even guarded by an env check.
- Logging of entire request/response objects or entire entity objects by reference, which risks incidentally dumping sensitive fields if the entity shape changes later.

## Example

```typescript
// ❌ Bad — unstructured, leaks sensitive data
this.logger.log(`Signing tx with key ${privateKey} for user ${userId}`);

// ✅ Good — structured, masked, milestone-tagged
this.logger.log('escrow.settlement.completed', {
  transactionId: tx.id,
  userId: user.id,
  escrowId: escrow.id,
  status: 'SETTLED',
  // privateKey / signature intentionally omitted from logs
});
```
